Package: bulkPop
Type: Package
Title: Simulate a propogating population with a set of genetic variants
Version: 0.1.2
Author: Eyal Ben-David
Maintainer: Dave Knull <dev@null.net>
Description: The package includes functions to build a genome object, that include variants, their physical and genetic positions, and names, and based on this object create and propagate a population.It is built specifically for c. elegans, and the recombination and cross functions are built to handle elegans genome structure with regards to sex chromosomes (xx/x0) and zeel-1/peel-1 selection, which is baked it.
License: MIT
LazyData: TRUE
Depends:
    R (>= 2.10)
Imports:
    bit,
    ggplot2,
    ggthemes,
    qtl,
    parallel,
    Rcpp (>= 0.12.5)
LinkingTo: Rcpp
RoxygenNote: 5.0.1
